name: 李老师不是你老师
content: It is reported that one of the reasons why investors flocked to the comment section of the US Embassy’s Weibo account was because the China Securities Regulatory Commission and all related accounts had banned comments.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On February 2, migrant workers demanded their wages at the headquarters of Guangzhou Jishi Construction Group Co., Ltd.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Following the comments section of the US Embassy and Eastmoney, netizens on Toutiao are not to be outdone.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On February 1, Wu Qiang, a cadre of the Hanjiang District Court of Putian City, Fujian Province, reported under his real name that the court's former president He Wenzhen and political director Huang Zhiqiang were suspected of buying and selling official positions.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On February 3, at the entrance of Xiongan Convention and Exhibition Center, a man wearing a national flag demanded his salary.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Previously, netizens were discussing that "the whole country is filled with an optimistic atmosphere":

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On February 1, a retired veteran who claimed to have participated in maintaining stability in Xinjiang and had been awarded the third-class merit posted a video saying that in August 2023, he bravely helped an underage girl in Langfang, Hebei, and was beaten by five people, resulting in fractures of the 2nd, 3rd and 4th lumbar vertebrae. To date, issues such as compensation have not been resolved.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On February 3, migrant workers from Shandong Rizhao Urban Investment Co., Ltd. demanded their wages.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Some netizens said that because they made an insignificant comment on the US Embassy’s Weibo, their Weibo, Sina Finance, and Alipay accounts were blocked or banned, and their cell phone IEMI codes were also blocked on Weibo, leading to the blocking of three accounts on their phone.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: One blogger thought that it was "very embarrassing" for the stock investors to collectively go to the US Embassy to speak, but many people in the comment section expressed their disagreement: "Anyway, it's not the stock investors who are embarrassed," "They eat meat and wash your marrow and don't let you cry out, they even invited a troupe to sing praises, so everyone can only go to the concession to vent their emotions."
